option.name: documentText

task.summary: Changed set extractor to leverage Lists instead of Serialize/Deserialize.
Created helpers for creating maps, but these won't work "as is" (see FIXMEs)
Copied various changes to library from experimental async branch were they were accidentally commited.
Copied various changes to library from experimental async branch were they were accidentally commited.
Using serialize/deserialize to solve typing problem, but this isn't a good solution.
Removed references to "homogenous" since not especially important to map extractors, except that the maps already be consistent with the specified key fields and any predicates provided.
Added example method to DAO_UserSelector for consistency with test code.
Renamed MapSwapper since it doesn't have much to do with SObjects.
Created a method to reverse index maps. Doesn't exactly replace the MapSwapper, but it achieves much the same purpose in a reusable way.
Enabled supporting none one-to-one key-value relationships in reverse index.
Extracted serialization of Maps to common methods.
Modified extractors to use loops instead of serialization because serialization breaks references.
Adding converting types via serialization/deserialization but named to point out that this dereferences.
Created a way to rebind objects for Dynamic SOQL.
Updated DAO classes to match revised framework.
Deleted support for arbitrary string clause (Which is probably broken now.)
Removed contact selector since its not valid for most orgs.
Renamed field to get query locator.
Created some tests for Product Selector
Refactored some DAOs to use FFLib; renamed interesting FFLib classes to make them "stand out".
Renamed some methods to provide a better DSL.
Selector is almost completely refactored EXCEPT it still expects an FF-like query factory and does not yet support WHERE objects.
Cleaned out comments and debug code.
